	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />You've hit upon the fundamental flaw in CopyNES.  Kev only made a few of them, and never made the complete schematics and software available so that others could duplicate it.  Not that he was under any obligation to do so, it's his intellectual property and he can do what he wants with it.  But this decision effectively killed the CopyNES.  Incidentally, Brian and his Devtendo are headed for the same fate apparently.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


