		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I was thinking about this too..but : how are you going to get an emulator to run your code at 1000-1FFF, 3000-3FFF, I can understand maybe testing out bits of code...but really..copynes does nothing to the output (display/sound) and I don't see any great advantage to testing in an emulator.
<br />
<br />As far as desoldering equipment - try cooking the nes board in cooking oil until it gets warm anough for the solder to melt. This is the best 'cheap' way that I've found. Seriously.

		

